The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, February 19, 2004 				 Pre-paid trio for the duped
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Theres good news for taxi victims. Three pre-paid taxi booths will be set up, in association with the traffic police, at the AJC Bose Road-Shakespeare Sarani crossing, Shyambazar and Dhakuria. 																								The decision was taken after a meeting on Wednesday, involving deputy commissioner of police (traffic) Peeyush Pandey, director of the public vehicles department (PVD) H. Mohan and representatives of the taxi associations. 																								The pre-paid booths, with telephones, will function till late at night, elaborated Pandey, adding that the number would be increased.																								Metro, in a series of reports, had highlighted the hooliganism after dark by a section of taxi drivers at Howrah station. The matter came up at the meeting, with both Pandey and Mohan urging the operators to safeguard passenger interest.																								Taxi operators later said a meeting would soon be convened to draw up a plan for pre-paid and post-paid taxi booths, round-the-clock, at Howrah and Sealdah stations.																								We will look at the interests of the taxi owners and drivers, but at the same time, they must protect the interests of the commuters, said Pandey.																								PVD officials said both police and operators have agreed to take action against taxi refusals. Please take down the number of the vehicle and inform us, was the operators message to the victimised commuters.
